1955;;The Woman for Joe;;British;;George More O'Ferrall;;Diane Cilento, George Baker;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Woman_for_Joe;;Midget George Wilson pulls strings to obtain a job in the circus for Mary, a Hungarian lady he's fallen madly in love with. Mary is happy to have the job, singing to the lions, but although she likes George, her feelings for circus owner Joe Harrop are stronger. The jealousy and tensions caused affect the running of the circus.